---
title: HITL Consent Challenge — All Paths (hitl_consent_mfa_mode)
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant B as Browser
    participant BFF as BFF<br/>(demo_api_server)
    participant TC as transactionConsentChallenge.js
    participant P1 as PingOne MFA

    %% ── SHARED: 428 gate + createChallenge ──────────────────────────────────
    Note over B,P1: ALL PATHS start here — 428 gate enforces consent requirement
    B->>BFF: POST /api/transactions (transfer, or withdrawal/deposit ≥ $250)
    BFF-->>B: 428 Precondition Required { type, amount, ...snapshot }
    B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge { type, amount, fromAccountId, ... }
    BFF->>TC: createChallenge() — transfers always; others if ≥ confirm_threshold_usd
    BFF-->>B: 201 { challengeId, expiresAt, snapshot }
    Note over B: User reviews details in TransactionConsentModal and ticks consent checkbox

    %% ── PATH 1: homegrown OTP (hitl_consent_mfa_mode = homegrown) ───────────
    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over B,TC: PATH 1 — mode = homegrown (BFF-generated OTP, any amount)
        B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/confirm
        BFF->>TC: confirmChallenge() → mode=homegrown → generates OTP, stores HMAC hash
        TC-->>BFF: { otpSent: true, otpExpiresAt, otpCodeFallback? }
        Note over BFF: BFF emails OTP via emailService (or returns otpCodeFallback in dev)
        BFF-->>B: 200 { otpSent: true, otpExpiresAt }
        Note over B: User enters 6-digit OTP from email
        B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/verify-otp { otp }
        BFF->>TC: verifyOtp() — timingSafeEqual(hash) → status = "confirmed"
        BFF-->>B: 200 { challengeId, confirmExpiresAt }
        B->>BFF: POST /api/transactions { consentChallengeId }
        BFF->>TC: verifyAndConsumeChallenge() — snapshot match, one-time use
        BFF-->>B: 200 transaction result
    end

    %% ── PATH 2: PingOne one-time OTP (hitl_consent_mfa_mode = onetime — DEFAULT) ─
    rect rgb(232, 240, 255)
        Note over B,P1: PATH 2 — mode = onetime (DEFAULT) — PingOne sends OTP, no device enrollment needed
        B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/confirm
        BFF->>TC: confirmChallenge() → mode=onetime → mfaService.getPingOneUserContact(userId)
        BFF->>P1: GET /environments/{envId}/users/{userId} (worker token)
        P1-->>BFF: { email, mobilePhone }

        alt Contact found (email or phone on P1 account)
            BFF->>TC: _initiateOnetimeOtp() → mfaService.initiateOneTimeOtp(userId, type, contact, userToken)
            BFF->>P1: POST /environments/{envId}/deviceAuthentications<br/>{ user.id, selectedDevice.oneTime: { type: EMAIL|SMS, email|phone } } (user token)
            P1-->>BFF: { id: daId, status: OTP_REQUIRED, _embedded.devices[0].email: "us**@..." }
            BFF->>TC: ch.oneTimePath=true, ch.daId, ch.otpExpiresAt
            BFF-->>B: 200 { otpSent: true, otpExpiresAt, maskedContact: "us**@example.com" }
            Note over B: "A code was sent to us**@example.com" — user enters 6-digit OTP
            B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/verify-otp { otp }
            BFF->>TC: getChallengePath() → "onetime" → verifyMfa()
            BFF->>P1: POST /environments/{envId}/deviceAuthentications/{daId}<br/>Content-Type: application/vnd.pingidentity.otp.check+json (worker token)
            P1-->>BFF: { status: COMPLETED }
            BFF->>TC: status = "confirmed"
            BFF-->>B: 200 { challengeId, confirmExpiresAt }
        else No contact on P1 account
            BFF->>TC: needsContact=true, ch.oneTimePath=true, ch.pendingContact=true
            BFF-->>B: 200 { needsContact: true }
            Note over B: UI shows contact-collection step — "Where should we send the code?"
            B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/confirm-contact { email | phone }
            BFF->>TC: confirmOnetimeContact() — validates format, calls _initiateOnetimeOtp()
            BFF->>P1: POST /environments/{envId}/deviceAuthentications<br/>{ selectedDevice.oneTime: { type, email|phone } } (user token)
            P1-->>BFF: { id: daId, status: OTP_REQUIRED, maskedContact }
            BFF->>TC: ch.status=otp_pending, ch.pendingContact=false
            BFF-->>B: 200 { otpSent: true, maskedContact }
            Note over B: User enters 6-digit OTP from PingOne
            B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/verify-otp { otp }
            BFF->>TC: verifyMfa() → verifyOneTimeOtp(daId, otp)
            BFF->>P1: POST /deviceAuthentications/{daId} otp.check (worker token)
            P1-->>BFF: { status: COMPLETED }
            BFF->>TC: status = "confirmed"
            BFF-->>B: 200 { challengeId, confirmExpiresAt }
        end

        B->>BFF: POST /api/transactions { consentChallengeId }
        BFF->>TC: verifyAndConsumeChallenge() — snapshot match, one-time use
        BFF-->>B: 200 transaction result
    end

    %% ── PATH 3: PingOne device-picker MFA (hitl_consent_mfa_mode = device_picker) ─
    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over B,P1: PATH 3 — mode = device_picker, amount ≥ confirm_stepup_threshold_usd ($500)
        Note over B,P1: (If amount < threshold, falls through to homegrown path)
        B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/confirm
        BFF->>TC: confirmChallenge() → mode=device_picker + amount≥$500 → mfaService.initiateDeviceAuth()
        BFF->>P1: POST /environments/{envId}/users/{userId}/deviceAuthentications (user token)
        P1-->>BFF: { id: daId, status: DEVICE_SELECTION_REQUIRED, _embedded.devices: [...] }
        BFF->>TC: ch.mfaPath=true, ch.daId, ch.devices
        BFF-->>B: 200 { mfaRequired: true, devices: [{ id, type, email|phone|... }] }
        Note over B: User sees device picker — selects enrolled device (EMAIL, SMS, FIDO2, etc.)
        B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/select-device { deviceId }
        BFF->>TC: selectMfaDevice() → mfaService.selectDevice(daId, deviceId, workerToken)
        BFF->>P1: POST /deviceAuthentications/{daId}<br/>Content-Type: application/vnd.pingidentity.device.select+json (worker token)
        P1-->>BFF: { status: OTP_REQUIRED | ASSERTION_REQUIRED | PUSH_CONFIRMATION_REQUIRED }
        BFF-->>B: 200 { otpSent: true }
        Note over B: User enters OTP received on selected device (or completes FIDO2 gesture)
        B->>BFF: POST /consent-challenge/:id/verify-otp { deviceId, otp | fido2Assertion }
        BFF->>TC: getChallengePath() → "mfa" → verifyMfa()
        BFF->>P1: mfaService.submitOtp(daId, deviceId, otp) — worker token
        P1-->>BFF: { status: COMPLETED }
        BFF->>TC: status = "confirmed"
        BFF-->>B: 200 { challengeId, confirmExpiresAt }
        B->>BFF: POST /api/transactions { consentChallengeId }
        BFF->>TC: verifyAndConsumeChallenge() — snapshot match, one-time use
        BFF-->>B: 200 transaction result
    end

    %% ── DEMO BYPASS ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Note over B,TC: OTP "123123" bypasses PingOne in paths 2 and 3 for demo environments
